# LICENCE

`iontrap-dynamics` uses a **split-licence architecture**, in line with T(h)reehouse +EC Corporate Design rule CD 0.3 and Design Principle 12 of [`WORKPLAN_v0.3.md`](WORKPLAN_v0.3.md). Different layers of the repository carry different licences; this file declares the split and points to the per-folder `LICENCE` files that carry the canonical terms.

## Summary of layers

| Path | Layer | Licence | SPDX |
|---|---|---|---|
| `WORKPLAN_v0.3.md`, `CONVENTIONS.md` (repo root) | Coastline docs | CC BY-SA 4.0 | `CC-BY-SA-4.0` |
| `docs/` — coastline material | Coastline docs | CC BY-SA 4.0 | `CC-BY-SA-4.0` |
| `docs/tutorials/` | Authored tutorials (Sail) | CC BY-NC-SA 4.0 | `CC-BY-NC-SA-4.0` |
| `src/`, `tests/`, `.github/`, build scripts | Code & tooling | MIT | `MIT` |
| `tools/` | Build / maintenance scripts | MIT | `MIT` |
| `assets/` | Design assets (consumed upstream) | MIT | `MIT` |

External fonts referenced by the docs site (IBM Plex Mono, Crimson Pro) are distributed under SIL OFL 1.1 (`OFL-1.1`) by their respective upstreams; they are not vendored in this repository.

## Coastline / Sail semantics

Per CD 0.9, `iontrap-dynamics` distinguishes:

- **Coastline** material — testable, binding constraints (this workplan, `CONVENTIONS.md`, architectural specs, the Boundary Decision Tree, result-schema documents) — licensed **CC BY-SA 4.0**.
- **Sail** material — authored, adaptive guidance (tutorials, pedagogical essays, Clock-School teaching material, worked-example narratives) — licensed **CC BY-NC-SA 4.0**.

The licence distinction is deliberate: Coastline is copy-left and non-commercial-permissive (reuse and adaptation encouraged, including in commercial teaching contexts); Sail is copy-left and non-commercial (authored teaching material should not be monetised by third parties without negotiation).

## Authoritative licence-text files

This file (`LICENCE`) declares the split; it is **not itself** a licence grant. Canonical licence text for each layer lives in the file named below. Any layer not explicitly delegating to its own folder-level file is governed by the corresponding canonical text at the repository root.

- [`LICENCE-MIT`](LICENCE-MIT) — canonical MIT grant covering `src/`, `tests/`, `tools/`, and `.github/`. Source files in these paths SHOULD carry an `SPDX-License-Identifier: MIT` header so the effective terms are machine-readable.
- [`assets/LICENCE`](assets/LICENCE) — MIT grant for the design assets in that folder (distributed from upstream `threehouse-plus-ec/cd-rules` under Model B, per the blueprint's prescribed per-folder declaration). Provenance recorded in [`assets/SOURCE.md`](assets/SOURCE.md).
- [`docs/LICENCE`](docs/LICENCE) — declares the internal CC BY-SA 4.0 / CC BY-NC-SA 4.0 split between Coastline docs and Sail tutorials within `docs/`. At present, the folder contains Coastline-facing entry pages only.

## Precedence

When folder content is mixed, the more restrictive licence applies unless an individual file declares otherwise via an `SPDX-License-Identifier` header. Coastline documents at the repository root (`WORKPLAN_v0.3.md`, `CONVENTIONS.md`) declare their own CC BY-SA 4.0 terms in their frontmatter; those declarations are authoritative for those files.

## Asset provenance (Model B, CD 0.10)

Design assets in `assets/` are distributed copies of material authored by `threehouse-plus-ec/cd-rules`, propagated under Model B: distributed copy with SHA-256 checksum and byte-size verification against the pinned upstream commit. See [`assets/SOURCE.md`](assets/SOURCE.md) for the full provenance record. Upstream licence (MIT) is preserved; no re-licensing occurs at the boundary.

## Changes and re-licensing

Changes to this split require a CHANGELOG entry and a migration note. Re-licensing of already-published material (e.g. narrowing a layer's terms) requires consent of all contributors to that layer, consistent with the copy-left obligations of CC BY-SA 4.0 and CC BY-NC-SA 4.0.

